{
  "stem": "8252.3",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So-- especially the Jews.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The Jews in Russian Army were picked out from among the Russian prisoners of war.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They were sent.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And there was also, very well guarded, separated from us, Americans and-- and British.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Now and I want to go back to Krems an der Donau and tell you that while they could separate the French and the Poles and the Yugoslavs, I have seen a company of British soldiers come in, into the camp, at military pace, in line, beautifully.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then they stop in front of the Kommandant's office, and the Kommandant comes out and says, Jews, three steps forward, and the whole company stepped forward.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They could not separate them because then the others didn't go for it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "That was British.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah, this pretty amazing.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That happened, of course, back in my story.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was in Krems.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I have seen that in Krems, which when we got into Austria.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that, you know, probably happened all over Germany several times, but that's the one I have seen.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was in the corner where Austria, Czechoslovakia, and Germany-- the prewar borders-- meet, in that area.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was about 50 villages that were evacuated, and this was a tremendous training camp for the German army.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I had-- have been assigned two horses and a wagon, and I was transporting things.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My job was to clean the horses in the morning, hook them up to-- to the-- to the wagon, and then just drive them around.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that allowed me, and people like me, to do two things.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "First, deal with the German and-- and the forced labor population for food.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
